Football:
7-12 Football Families,
We will begin football practice on 9/14 for grades 7-12 on M,W,F following our lifting and running workouts. These practices should begin around 5pm and be done around 6:30pm. On Saturdays we will host scrimmages on the game field starting at 6 pm for junior high and 7pm for 9-12. These scrimmages will all be flag scrimmages except for the final 9-12 scrimmage where the kids will wear pads. These practices will last for 3 weeks.
The lifting and running opportunities on M,W,F after school are limited because of only allowing a limited number of kids in the weight room. We are currently not able to take anymore kids in the facility, but if kids want to come and run outside they are welcome to on these days.

post_text: Great job last night at the Byron CC meet in a tough 3 team field consisting of PI, Stewartville, and host school Byron. Both JH boys and girls teams finished 2nd overall. The JH boys were led by Ryder Schmidt (6th) and Jackson Hudson (8th). Leading the JH girls were Taylor Brown (6th), Riley Carlson (9th), and Monica Sems (10th). The JV boys placed 1st led by Lucas Williams (1st), Andrew Taggart (3rd), Jamison Rosane (4th), Kaedyn Peterson-Rucker (5th). The JV girls also finished 1st led by Alivia Levi (1st), River Weissgerber (2nd), Ashley Pederson (3rd). The Varsity girls placed 3rd led by Brooklyn Horton (7th) and Brooklyn Radtke (8th). The Varsity boys were champions by 1 point over Byron. They were led by race champion Tanner Horton and Braxton Osterhaus (4th). The team is next in action Tuesday at Ferndale Country Club in Rushford and Thursday home at PI golf course.

post_text:
The Boys PIZM Wildcats defeated the Lake City Tigers 3-2 in a 7 pm game played in Lake City. Lake City scored first off a corner kick and then scored a 2nd time in the first half. PZIM came back to the game before the first half ended with a Drew Christopherson scoring off a header from an assist from Dan Mikaeo. Then Dan Mikeao made the timing goal off an assist from Mark Quintero. In the second half, PIZM’s Mark Quintero scored the winning goal off an assist from Drew Christopherson.

JV tied 2:2 and JH won 9:1.

post_text:
The Pine Island Cross Country Team had a great first meet last night at the PI golf course. Leading the varsity boys to a 2nd place finish were Tanner Horton (3rd). Braxton Osterhaus (5th), and Julian Rauk (9th). Leading the varsity girls to a close 2nd place finish over Kasson Mantorville/Triton were Brooklyn Horton (6th) and Brooklyn Radtke (7th). Lake City won the team title for both varsity boys and girls.

The JV races were highlighted by Matthew Horkey winning the JV race in his first CC meet. Andrew Taggart (4th) and Sam Warneke (5th) also helped pace the JV boys to a team victory over Lake City. Madeline Johnston (7th) led the incomplete JV girls team.

The JH boys and girls each won the meet and each achieved a perfect team score of 15 points. Leading the JH Boys were Jamison Rosane (1st), Drew Sailer (2nd), and Ryder Schmidt (3rd). Leading the JH Girls were River Weissgerber (1st), Alivia Levi (2nd), and Ashley Pederson (3rd).

Full results can be found at: https://results.wayzatatiming.com/meets/6261
The team is back in action next Tuesday at Byron.

The MSHSL voted today on Fall sports. Not many details are available at this time. However, Cross Country, Boys' Soccer, and Girls' Soccer will start August 17 with reduction in season and games. Details on registration will come soon.

Football and Volleyball were considered a higher risk, and their seasons have been moved to the Spring. The thought of looking at a 4th season for MN (possibly early spring with shortened season) and Spring sports would go more into June... Again details are not developed at this time. More details will come when we hear.

Work day/Year: Full time on student attendance days

Middle School 7th Grade Language Arts Long Term Substitute

Position Type: Long Term Substitute

Date Posted: June 12, 2020

Location: Pine Island School Middle School ISD 255

Work day/Year: Long term substitute starting in the 2020-2021 school year

Application Deadline: Open Until Filled

Job Summary: Independent School District #255 Pine Island is seeking a long term substitute to teach language arts in the 7th grade. This position would be responsible for teaching the 7th grade Minnesota English Language Arts Standards in an effective, efficient, and creative way. We are looking for a candidate who enjoys creating engaging curriculum and delivering content in new and exciting ways! All students are one-to-one with Chromebooks and there are opportunities for support to all staff members in the areas of technology, curriculum, and professional development .

Qualification Required: A Minnesota teaching license to teach language arts in the 7th grade.

Apply online at.www.pineisland.k12.mn.us

The Track and Field Coaches Association awards Academic All State each season. This year it is based on a cumulative gpa of 3.6 and above AND one or more of the following:
state competitor in 2019
all conference in 2019
met the state honor roll standard in one or more events in the 2019 season
a 2020 senior
Congratulations to the following track and field athletes for earning Academic All State for the 2020 season:

Girls
Annika Adelsman - 12
Megan Gerhart - 12
Cora Heiden - 12
Taylor House - 12
Brooke Sinning - 12
Jaci Newman - 11
Kiley House - 10
Lauren Wangsness - 10

Boys
Connor Bailey - 12
Cole Groven - 12
Carter O'Reilly - 12
Isaac Schmoll - 12
Will Warneke - 12
Mason Pike - 11
Zack Ihde - 10
Mark Quintero Bungert - 10
Jarod White - 10
Dylan Holzer - 12

In addition, using the top 10 cumulative gpas of 2020 team members in grades 9-12, both boys and girls teams earned the gold academic standard. The boys averaged a perfect 4.0! The girls were not far behind with an average of 3.9862.

Congratulations to all of our student athletes!

Being able to support our school and community by volunteering is what PTO does! This school year we have earned $1,564.00 through BOX TOPS! 10 cents truly adds up!

💵💵

What has PTO used these funds for WITHIN THE 2 MONTHS!?
--------------

--Panther masks for Pine Island's Seniors to wear during
graduation
--Individual picture yard signs for each senior
--Over 1,100 goodie bags given out during device pick-up
(preschool-11th grade)
--A THANK YOU, local gift card to each and every staff
member in the district, during Staff Appreciation Week.
--Virtual Spirit Days through social media
--The Staff Parade at the beginning of the school closure!
--Student/Parent Tribute Video to our incredible Pine Island
Staff!

Pine Island Public School District is currently seeking a mechanic in the transportation department. This position includes am and pm route driving, as well as other seasonal duties as directed. The ideal candidate would possess knowledge in the following areas:
diesel repair and maintenance
air and hydraulic brake systems
general automotive repair and maintenance abilities

We have training available for the Class B CDL needed for this position. We offer competitive compensation. Application deadline is June 15.

Apply online at www.pineisland.k12.mn.us

Middle School 7th Grade Language Arts Long Term Substitute

Position Type: Long Term Substitute

Date Posted: May 12, 2020

Location: Pine Island School Middle School ISD 255

Work day/Year: Long term substitute starting in the 2020-2021 school year

Application Deadline: Open Until Filled

Job Summary: Independent School District #255 Pine Island is seeking a long term substitute to teach language arts in the 7th grade. This position would be responsible for teaching the 7th grade Minnesota English Language Arts Standards in an effective, efficient, and creative way. We are looking for a candidate who enjoys creating engaging curriculum and delivering content in new and exciting ways! All students are one-to-one with Chromebooks and there are opportunities for support to all staff members in the areas of technology, curriculum, and professional development .

Qualification Required: A Minnesota teaching license to teach language arts in the 7th grade.

Apply online at www.pineisland.k12.mn.us

Spanish Teacher
Position Type: Spanish
Date Posted: May 11, 2020
Location: Pine Island Schools ISD 255
Work day/Year: 1 FTE, 2020-2021

Closing Date For Applications: Open until filled

Job Summary: Independent School District #255 Pine Island is seeking a Spanish teacher for the 2020-21 school year. The Spanish teacher will be responsible for effectively and efficiently delivering instruction in Spanish I, Spanish II, and Exploratory Spanish at our 5-12 site. This candidate must be trained in or be willing to be trained in and teach with comprehensible input/TPRS approach to Spanish instruction. Pine Island Schools is a growing district with over 1,300 students, and is located ten minutes north of Rochester. Letter of Application, district application, transcripts, resume, and 3 letters of reference should be sent to Mitchel Schiltz, High School Principal.

Qualifications:
Current Minnesota licensure.

Application Procedure: Apply online at www.pineisland.k12.mn.us

We know it's hard to think about school supply shopping, especially right now. But, what we do know is there will be a 1st Day of School this fall! That is why PTO is so excited to announce their continued partnership with 1st Day School Supplies.

This year, 1st Day School Supplies is going to help parents and teachers get the exact supplies needed for next school year without the RISK of shopping at Walmart, Target or Staples.

1st Day School Supplies is convenient, easy and hassle free! Plus, they have guaranteed competitive prices on the highest quality brands including the germ fighting brands like Purell and Clorox. So, with all the uncertainty this summer will bring, why not check school supply shopping off your list.

post_text:
In an immediate response to the closure of MN Schools, I wanted to assure you that we have been working on a comprehensive plan for a variety of situations, and will now focus on our closure plan. Be assured that we will offer emergency childcare to our parents working in healthcare and emergency services, to include medical, law enforcement, and first responders. We will also be providing meal service in a limited format to those in need. Our detailed plan will be published later this evening. We will also be posting hours for families who may need to pick-up medication or other items. All school events, community education activities, athletics are all canceled until Monday, March 30th, at the earliest.

While we are in uncharted territory, please know our school is committed to serving our students, families and community. Together, we stand strong.

Tammy Champa

The Minnesota State High School League is immediately cancelling the Girls' Basketball State Tournament.

Additionally, all Boys' Section and State Basketball Tournaments have been cancelled.

Section Speech Tournament events for the week of March 15-21 have been postponed indefinitely.

Additional details and information on other upcoming events including Spring Activities will be shared later today.

post_text:
Description: Q-Comp Coach, 185 days

Job Summary: Pine Island Public Schools highly supports the professional development of all of our staff. Since 2015, the Pine Island District has offered all licensed staff the opportunity to participate in our Q-Comp program. The district supports three full-time positions to support classroom teachers with a series of observation cycles to build upon and support the work of each individual classroom teacher.

Qualifications: Valid MN Teaching License with a preference for a Master's Degree. Preference will be given to candidates with a minimum of 5 years teaching experience.

Working Conditions: Duties are generally performed in a typical school setting where there are minimal environmental hazards and risks.

Application Procedure:
Apply Online at www.pineisland.k12.mn.us

Date Posted: February 27, 2020
Location: Pine Island Schools ISD 255

Qualifications:
Current Minnesota licensure for Social Studies

Application Procedure: Apply online at www.pineisland.k12.mn.us

If you are at least 13 years old and would like to be a soccer referee or know someone who does? What a great way to understand the rule of the game and earn some extra cash.

Southern Minnesota Soccer Referee Association is looking for ambitious young men and women to become USSF certified soccer referees.

Go to www.minnesotasrc.com to begin your registration. On the Minnesotasrc homepage, there is a “new referee info” button. Click on it and it gives you all the information needed to register as a new referee. There is also a link on this page for parents to learn about the young referee’s expectations and challenges.

Step 4 refers to attending a clinic. There are many available at various times throughout the state, but there is only one in Rochester.

Where: Calvary Evangelist Free Church
5500 55th St NW Rochester

When: March 21, 2020

If you have any questions, please contact smsraedu@gmail.com

Attention students (Grades 10-12): Pine Island High School will be offering the ASVAB test on Wednesday, April 8, at 8:00 a.m. in the Forum Room. The ASVAB is an aptitude test that measures strengths and weaknesses and predicts future academic and occupational success in the military. Students interested in taking the test must sign up in the high school office by Thursday, March 12th. This can be a great
opportunity for students looking at the military and/or students who would like to learn more about how their individual strengths and interests may translate into the work of work.

Pine Island Public Schools is currently looking for a Night Shift Lead Custodian available 2:30pm – 11:00pm (Must be available to work day hours during the summer and breaks).

We have a good team and are searching for a hard-working leader that can manage the night crew, handle light administration tasks and be responsible for cleaning and maintenance duties.

We are building a strong team that focuses on great service, professionalism, kindness and respect with strong accountability. Our candidate must be a good fit in our culture.

Maintenance and custodial knowledge and aptitude is a must. Basic computer skills will also be needed. A boilers license is preferred, but not required. Hourly wage range between $20 and $25 per hour (with an additional $.70/ hr. incentive for night work), depending on experience and a boilers license.

Application Procedure:
Apply Online at www.pineisland.k12.mn.us

shared_text:
Bob Brown
February 8 at 12:42 PM ·

In 43 years in the sports writing business you meet a lot of interesting people. Here’s another:
I had the pleasure to write about Pine Island MN High School’s storied baseball coach Craig Anderson. When he retired in 2016 after a 36-year stint at Pine Island his record was 505-359. He also coached American Legion and Babe Ruth baseball. His 1995 Legion team won a state championship. Craig received a bushel of honors. Among them was becoming the first Minnesotan to be inducted into the National High School Hall of Fame. But the most important thing he did had nothing to do with baseball. He donated a kidney to younger brother Kevin. “His kidneys were failing and if he was to have any quality of life, he needed a kidney transplant,” Craig said. “I volunteered to give him one of mine and when we found out I was a match we went ahead with the transplant. That’s the least I could do for a brother. That was more important than a baseball game.”

PLEASE CALL COMMUNITY ED TO REGISTER 356-8876

Sunshine and Roses Parent Child Date Night

Join Sunshine and Roses for a fun filled, memory making date night with your favorite artist! The class will be a diptych painting which means each painter will have their own canvas. The paintings will come together to create one beautiful painting. Beginners are welcome, and you do not need any Art experience (most of the participants do not have any). More than two painters can be in a group (if a parent has 2 children for example); just let them know when you register. $24 per painter includes 11x14 canvas, all supplies, and step by step instructions.

Painters will get to choose between a winter or a spring scene. Both choices will be taught at the same class.

Date: Monday, February 10
Time 4:15 – 5:15 pm
Location: Pine Island Elementary School Art Room 201
Fee: $24

Instructor is Penni Kittelson - Owner of Sunshine and Roses Traveling Art Studio

Kailee, Carter, and their parents will be honored and recognized at the Section 1A and 1AA Boys Basketball Championships on Thursday, March 12, at the Mayo Civic Center Arena. They will also attend the State "Triple A" Banquet in Minneapolis and participate in an on-court ceremony at the State BBB Tournament at the Target Center on Saturday, March 21.

post_text:
The Scripps 2020 Pine Island District Spelling Bee was held on Wednesday, January 15.

Seven participants from grades 6-8 battled for seven rounds before 8th grader Grace Schroeder was named the Bee Champion. Her winning word was tapestry. This is Grace's second appearance in the final School Bee finishing as runner up last year to Hans Benike who was also in this year's finals.

The other contestants consisted of three 6th graders: 3rd place finisher, Owen Rueb, Will Taylor, and second place finisher, Kaden Chim. In seventh and eighth grade: Archer LaRue (7), Sam Muller (7) also second appearance, and Hans Benike (8).

Grace will move forward in competition on February 11, at 9:00 AM to the Regional Spelling Bee at the Southeast Services Cooperative.

The other contestants consisted of three 6th graders: 3rd place finisher, Owen Rueb, Will Taylor, and second place finisher, Kaden Chim. In seventh and eighth grade: Archer LaRue (7), Sam Muller (7) also second appearance, and Hans Benike (8).

Grace will move forward in competition on February 11, at 9:00 AM to the Regional Spelling Bee at the Southeast Services Cooperative.

Sunshine and Roses— Winter Scene

In June we painted on large 16x20 canvases, and the kids loved it. This beautiful winter scene will be created using the large canvas. Fee: $24

Congratulations the gymnastics team on their win at the Austin Invite Saturday with a team score of 138.7. Placing for PI/ZM were
Vault: Sawyer Gorman 2nd, Jaci Newman 3rd and Cora Heiden 4th
Bars: Jaci Newman 1st, Sawyer Gorman 2nd and Mckenzie Cordes 5th
Beam: McKenzie Cordes 1st, Jaci Newman 2nd, and Cora Heiden 4th
Floor: Sawyer Gorman 1st, Mckenzie Cordes 2nd and Jaci Newman 5th
All Around: Jaci Newman 2nd, Sawyer Gorman 3rd and McKenzie Cordes 4th.
Great job ladies!!!
